<dl id="n14067d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14067d">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14067d"> 67(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 843 Verdun</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The words of Wilhelm Jordan, uttered with respect to the Thousand-year Anniversary of Germany&apos;s Birth (1843), when he alluded to the Treaty of <mark>Verdun (843)</mark>, ring far truer in their application to the present day, without giving the least cause for pessimism; for Spiritual Science is giving us the power to reach for the third time in the direction needed.&rdquo; <small> Ernst Boldt, <a name="BFLS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BFLS"><cite title="source">From Luther to Steiner</cite></a>, (1921) 35</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
